N20050526-0010

- Run Infer on JDT/Core
- got the following exception while resolving the type constraints

To additional observations:

- I had to increase the heap size to 512MB to be able to process all CUs
- when I encountered the exception I was in the debugger. One of the fields of
  the type set was a linked hash map with lots of capture type bindings.
  Could it be that the cpature types are tricking us now since they are always
  unique instances ?

*** Bug 97245 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***

Fixed the AFE and made sure we don't use capture bindings.
Will further investigate heap consumption.

ASTs are now created in batches, which greatly reduces heap consumption in big
projects. Furthermore, autoboxing support has been improved and avoids
generating constraint variables where not required.
Verified in N20050609-0010.  Markus, please update state to VERIFIED
